ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Since the course is compulsory for English PhD students I wouldn't recommend it as such, but I would say that it can be highly valuable if you make the most of it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I think this class really helped me to think about how the two major facets of our profession--our research and our teaching--are so intertwined. Being "Teaching Practicum," of course, this class had as its main goal to teach us how to teach. And, in my case at least, I think it really did help me to prepare for being a TF next year.

I got a lot out of the discussions we had in 990, as well as from the teaching observations and experience that the course requires; I think I have a clearer and better informed perspective on undergraduate teaching as a result.
